Date: 7th July 1809 - Size: Small - Location: Girona, Catalonia\\Scenario
Briefing: Third Siege of Girona: Assault on Monjuich - On receiving
some 4,000 - albeit poor-quality - Italian reinforcements, Verdier
had 14,000 men and felt strong enough to lay siege to Girona
on 24 May. The Spanish garrison under Alvarez consisted of 5,700
regulars and about 1,200 local militia. Verdier, who had experienced
vicious street fighting at Zaragoza, established regular siege
works. On 19 June the outlying San Luis and San Narciso forts
were captured after an intense bombardment in preparation for
an attack on Monjuich. By 7 July a viable breach had been made
in the defences and Verdier launched a dawn assault.\\Recommended
Rules: Default\\Note: This scenario is designed for a French
player against a Spanish A/I
